{{Infobox organization | name = Fondo Nacional de Desarrollo Científico y Tecnológico | logo = Logotipo del CONICYT.png | logo_caption = Logo for the National Commission for Scientific and Technological Research (CONICYT). | type= public | established = 1984 | headquarters = {{flagicon|Chile}} [[Santiago de Chile|Santiago]], [[Chile]] | parent_organization = CONICYT | mission = Funding scientific research | website = [http://www.conicyt.cl/fondecyt/ www.conicyt.cl/fondecyt] }}
The '''National Fund for Scientific and Technological Development''' (Spanish: ''Fondo Nacional de Desarrollo Científico y Tecnológico''), abbreviated '''FONDECYT''', is the main public fund of the [[Government of Chile]] to promote basic scientific and technological research in all areas of knowledge. It is managed by the National Commission for Scientific and Technological Research ([[CONICYT]]).
The fund was established in 1981 and began operations in 1982.<ref>{{cite book|title=FONDECYT: un análisis de su evolución (1982-1995)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N-xcAAAAMAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Corporación de Promoción Universitaria|page=3|language=es-ES}}</ref> Since then it has funded more than 16,000 research projects.<ref>{{cite web|title=FONDECYT: Historia|url=http://www.conicyt.cl/fondecyt/sobre-fondecyt/historia/|publisher=CONICYT|language=es-ES}}</ref> In 1991 CONICYT opened a second fund, FONDEF (The Science & Technology Development Fund), with the aim of promoting public&ndash;private collaboration in research and development.<ref>{{cite web|title=FONTEC and FONDEF: Driving Chilean technological development|url=https://innovationpolicyplatform.org/sites/default/files/rdf_imported_documents/FONTEC-FONDEF.pdf|author=The Innovation Policy Platform|year=2013|publisher=World Bank}}</ref>
== Selection of projects == The program provides financial support for projects selected under three headings: * Regular selection: for established researchers. * Selection for the Initiation of Research: opened in 2006 for young and emerging researchers. * Chilean Postdoctoral selection: for early career scientists to perform postdoctoral research in Chile.
