[[Image:Jan Smuts 1947.jpg|thumb|Smuts in 1947]] '''''Holism and Evolution''''' is a 1926 book by [[South Africa]]n statesman [[Jan Smuts]], in which he coined the word "[[holism]]",<ref name="OttoBubandt2011">{{cite book |author1=Ton Otto |author2=Nils Bubandt |title=Experiments in Holism: Theory and Practice in Contemporary Anthropology |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EGLPkWMgpIcC |date=2 August 2011 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=978-1-4443-5185-9 |page=252}}</ref><ref name="Freeman2005">{{cite journal |author=Freeman J |title=Towards a definition of holism |journal=Br J Gen Pract |year= 2005 |volume= 55 |issue= 511 |pages= 154–5 |pmid=15720949 |doi= |pmc=1463203 }}</ref> although Smuts' meaning is different from the modern concept of holism.<ref name=Poynton>{{cite journal |last=Poynton |first=J.C. |date=1987 |title=Smuts's Holism and Evolution sixty years on |url= |journal=Transactions of the Royal Society of South Africa |publisher= |volume=46 |issue=3 |pages=181–189 |doi=10.1080/00359198709520121}}<!--|access-date=9 January 2016--></ref> Smuts defined holism as the "fundamental factor operative towards the creation of wholes in the universe."<ref name="Smuts1927">{{cite book |author=J.C. Smuts |title=Holism and evolution |url=https://archive.org/stream/holismandevoluti032439mbp/holismandevoluti032439mbp_djvu.txt |year=1927 |publisher=Рипол Классик |isbn=978-5-87111-227-4}}</ref>
The book was part of a broader trend of interest in holism in European and colonial academia during the early twentieth century.<ref name="OttoBubandt2011"/> Smuts' philosophy of holism was based in the thoughts behind his earlier book ''[[Walt Whitman]]: A Study in the Evolution of Personality'', written during his time in Cambridge.<ref>Jan C Smuts: Walt Whitman – ''a Study in the Evolution of Personality'', Wayne State University Press 1973</ref><ref>Hancock – ''Smuts: 1. The Sanguine Years, 1870–1919'', p. 28</ref> He described a "process-orientated, hierarchical view of nature" and has been influential among criticisms of [[reductionism]].<ref name=Poynton/> Smuts' formulation of holism has also been linked with his political-military activity, especially his aspiration to create a league of nations.<ref name=Crafford1943>{{cite book |last=Crafford |first= F.S. |title=Jan Smuts: A Biography |year=1943 |publisher=Kessinger Publishing |page=140 |isbn= 1-4179-9290-5}}</ref>
==References== {{reflist}}
