ile:Roland Eotvos.jpg|70px]] |- |[[Heinrich Kayser]] |1853–1940 |German |[[Wavenumber]] |[[Wavenumber|kayser]] |[[File:Heinrich Kayser.jpg|70px]] |- |[[J. J. Thomson|Joseph John Thomson]] |1856–1940 |British |[[Mass-to-charge ratio]] |[[thomson (unit)|thomson]] (Th) |[[File:J.J Thomson.jpg|70px]] |- |[[Pierre Curie]] [[Marie Curie]] |1859–1906 1867–1934 |French Polish-French |[[Radioactivity]] |[[curie]] (Ci) |[[File:Pierre Curie by Dujardin c1906.jpg|70px]][[File:Marie Curie c1920.jpg|70px]] |- |[[Heinrich Mache]] |1876–1954 |[[Austrians|Austrian]] |[[Radioactivity]] |[[Mache (unit)|Mache]] (ME) |[[File:Mache-Heinrich-(1876-1954)a.jpg|70px]] |- |[[Peter Debye]]||1884–1966||Dutch||[[Electric dipole moment]]||[[debye]] (D)||[[File:Debije-boerhaave.jpg|70px]] |- |[[Karl Guthe Jansky]]||1905–1950||American||[[Irradiance|Spectral Irradiance]]||[[Jansky]] (JY)||[[File:Karl Jansky.jpg|70px]] |}
